<s> Thank you Brian, I've hopefully captured these tweaks and added the following paragraph: This type is used by "bignum" values such as RSAKeyValue and DSAKeyValue.  </s>
<s> If a value can be of type base64Binary or ds:CryptoBinary they are defined as base64Binary.  </s>
<s> For example, if the signature algorithm is RSA or DSA then SignatureValue represents a bignum and could be ds:CryptoBinary.  </s>
<s> However, if HMAC-SHA1 is the signature algorithm then SignatureValue could have leading zero octets that must be preserved.  </s>
<s> Thus SignatureValue is generically defined as of type base64Binary.  </s>
